    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Order containing around nine living species in four families, members of which do not have front incisor teeth or molars, or have poorly-developed molars. The origins of the order can be traced back as far as the early Tertiary about 60 million years ago.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
